The Indian Cultural Association, Lagos branch, has held the 2019 annual Republic Day flag hoisting ceremony in Lagos to mark the 70th Republican anniversary of India. The event, which attracted Indians of various disciplines and callings, especially, those resident in Lagos and other parts of Nigeria, was attended and coordinated by the secretary of the association, Sanjeev Tandon, the immediate past president of Rotary Club of Lagos Island, District 9110 Nigeria, and vice president, Projects, Kewalram Chnrai Group Ltd. The event was celebrated by the young and old Indian nationals, whose allegiance to their fatherland was displayed to demonstrate to their Nigerian and other nationals resident in Nigeria the need to show allegiance to their fatherland. Sanjeev Tandon performed the 2019 Indian Republic Day flag hoisting ceremony.